# WHAT IT IS
#   mevlog is "EVM activity log monitoring CLI" — a Revm-powered
#   block-range tx querier and TUI for the Ethereum mempool and
#   confirmed-block stream.  It speaks alloy-rs `Provider` against
#   any EVM-compatible JSON-RPC endpoint (Ethereum mainnet, L2s,
#   sidechains discovered via the ChainList registry), persists
#   transaction selectors + decoded calldata to a local SQLite
#   index built from the Sourcify export, and reconstructs each
#   transaction through a Revm executor (with `revm-inspectors`)
#   so EVM trace, call sequence, opcode-level state diff, and
#   storage delta are queryable post-hoc.  ENS name and reverse-
#   lookup helpers are bundled, as is a debug-trace RPC
#   capability check, a TUI mode (feature `tui`), an MCP server
#   (feature `mcp`), and a dev-only signatures DB seeder
#   (feature `seed-db`).
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from crates/mevlog/bin/main.rs
#                       MLArgs / MLSubcommand and the per-command
#                       `cmd/<name>.rs` `Args` structs — clap 4
#                       with derive feature)
#   mevlog [GLOBAL OPTIONS] <SUBCOMMAND> [args...]
#
#   Global options:
#     --color <MODE>                 Color output mode
#                                    (auto|always|never)
#                                    [default: auto]
#     --format <FMT>                 Output format
#                                    (json|json-pretty|csv|table)
#                                    [default: json-pretty]
#                                    `csv` and `table` are
#                                    query-only
#
#   Subcommands:
#     query | q                      Query txs within a block range
#       -b, --blocks <RANGE>           Block range (e.g.
#                                      "22030899", "latest",
#                                      "22030800:22030900",
#                                      "50:latest", "50:")
#       --latest-offset <N>            Get N-offset latest block
#       --max-range <N>                Maximum allowed range size
#       --batch-size <N>               Fetch batch size
#                                      [default: 100]
#       --sql <SQL>                    Custom read-only SQL against
#                                      local txs DB
#       (plus SharedOpts: --evm-trace, --evm-calls, --evm-ops,
#        --evm-state-diff and ConnOpts: --rpc-url, --chain-id)
#
#     update-db                      Update signatures database
#                                    from Sourcify
#
#     chains                         List all available chains
#                                    from ChainList
#
#     chain-info                     Show detailed chain information
#                                    (chain_id, name, currency,
#                                    explorer URL, RPC URLs,
#                                    response times)
#
#     debug-available                Check if RPC supports
#                                    debug_tracing (debug_trace*)
#
#     ens-resolve                    Resolve an ENS name to an
#                                    address
#
#     ens-lookup                     Reverse-resolve an address to
#                                    an ENS name
#
#     mcp                            Start MCP server (feature
#                                    `mcp`)
#
#     seed-db                        [Dev] Seed signatures DB from
#                                    Sourcify export (feature
#                                    `seed-db`)
#
#     tui                            Run TUI (feature `tui`)
#
#   Standard clap auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Show version
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `alloy = { version = "1", features =
#   ["full"] }` declared in crates/mevlog/Cargo.toml plus `revm =
#   "33"` (Ethereum-Foundation-stewarded Revm executor) and
#   `revm-inspectors = "0.33"` — `alloy` is THE canonical Rust
#   Ethereum SDK maintained by Paradigm + the Alloy Working Group
#   (alloy-rs/alloy, 1.8K+ stars, the successor to gakonst/ethers-
#   rs).  alloy-rs ships the typed `alloy::primitives` module
#   (`Address`, `B256`, `U256`, `Bytes`, `FixedBytes<N>`,
#   `Selector`), the `alloy::sol!` macro (re-export of ethers-rs's
#   abigen replacement that produces typed contract bindings from
#   Solidity ABI/JSON), the `alloy::providers::Provider` trait
#   with `RootProvider`, `HttpProvider`, `WsProvider`, `IpcProvider`,
#   per-network fillers (`GasFiller`, `BlobGasFiller`, `NonceFiller`,
#   `ChainIdFiller`), `alloy::rpc::types::*` for eth_getBlockBy*
#   /eth_getTransaction*/eth_call/eth_subscribe payloads, the
#   `alloy::transports::http` ureq/reqwest transport stack, the
#   `alloy::network::AnyNetwork` polymorphic abstraction, the
#   `alloy::pubsub::Subscription<T>` async stream, and JSON-RPC
#   error mapping.  mevlog's `crates/mevlog/src/lib.rs` defines
